  "title": "currentRefinedValues adds empty div",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nThe currentRefinedValues widget renders html that contains a seemingly useless div. This makes it impossible to style the element following BEM, as I also cannot assign a class to this element trough cssClasses. I was mostly wondering if there is a reason for this div to exist?\r\n\r\nSee the generated html here, the imo dubious element is the third:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<div class=\"ais-root ais-current-refined-values\">\r\n  <div class=\"ais-body ais-current-refined-values--body\">\r\n    <div>\r\n      <div class=\"ais-current-refined-values--list search-interface-row search-interface-row--curent-refined-values\">\r\n        <div class=\"ais-current-refined-values--item search-interface-row__tag\">\r\n          <a class=\"ais-current-refined-values--link\" href=\"#\">\r\n            <div>≤ 5 <span class=\"ais-current-refined-values--count\">0</span></div>\r\n          </a>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <a class=\"ais-current-refined-values--clear-all\" href=\"#\">\r\n        <div>Clear all</div>\r\n      </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Generate an instance of currentRefinedValues\r\n2. Activate some filter\r\n3. See the div\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nClean html with no empty/unnamed divs\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - Browser (Chrome)\r\n - Version 2.10.1\r\n",
